[{"question":"The charter Tony Soprano in the lexicon of television?","answer":"I think it\u0027s at the top because I think, you know, television forever was, you know, consumed with creating a lead charter who would be, you know, likable and I think he made him -- he made this incredibly scary guy, who in many ways, extremely likable at the same time.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":38,"aSentId":39},{"question":"What kind of shape was he in there?","answer":"He was -- he was in a jovial mood, Piers.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":117,"aSentId":118},{"question":"Would you go along with that?","answer":"I would agree completely with that.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":144,"aSentId":145},{"question":"But what is your reaction?","answer":"Well, I was shocked.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":169,"aSentId":170},{"question":"What do you think?","answer":"Well, it will be right up there.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":200,"aSentId":201},{"question":"You mean like Vegas?","answer":"No, not Vegas.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":226,"aSentId":227},{"question":"What, you mean like a hospital with the padded rooms and the straight jackets?","answer":"No, no straight jackets.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":229,"aSentId":230},{"question":"What are you picking up there?","answer":"Yes, definitely, Piers.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":306,"aSentId":307},{"question":"Were you aware, were the cast aware of any health issues?","answer":"Well, at that time -- this -- we worked together a long time ago, and he was -- it\u0027s funny because he was just beginning -- when I worked with James, \"The Sopranos\" had not yet aired, so nobody knew what it was.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":329,"aSentId":330},{"question":"Is that pretty much, Kevin, how all the cast viewed him?","answer":"Again, I can\u0027t speak for everyone else, but that was certainly the impression I got.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":341,"aSentId":342},{"question":"How did Tony Soprano come into your life and into ours?","answer":"I got the script and I remember reading it and I was laughing out loud.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":377,"aSentId":378},{"question":"In what way?","answer":"You know, suave, good looking Mafioso guy.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":383,"aSentId":384},{"question":"What is your reaction to his very sad, untimely death today?","answer":"Well, I\u0027m shocked and I\u0027m, you know, really incredibly sad like everybody else.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":407,"aSentId":408},{"question":"He didn\u0027t seem very fit, and it\u0027s probably -- don\u0027t want to speculate about what happened to him but in terms of his capacity to do these kind of roles, you as a viewer, what did you -- what did you make of his power as a figure, physically and mentally?","answer":"He is very powerful.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":433,"aSentId":434},{"question":"Quite brooding, wasn\u0027t he?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":439,"aSentId":440},{"question":"Jeffrey, we\u0027re talking a little bit about \"The Sopranos\" but he was also a great movie actor, wasn\u0027t he?","answer":"He was.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":473,"aSentId":474},{"question":"Why aren\u0027t you interested in the guy that\u0027s driving the car?","answer":"I think he was taken aback himself by the scale of fame that came with the role and he really, I think, always found that a little awkward to deal with.","docId":"130619pmt","qSentId":511,"aSentId":512}]